==English==

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-æŋɡəl|-æŋɡəl]]

===Verb===
'''to dangle'''  (''intransitive'')
# to [[hang]] [[loosely]] with the ability to [[swing]]
#:''His feet would '''dangle''' in the water''
#([[ice hockey]])(slang) the action of preforming a move or [[deke]] with the puck in order to get past a defender or goalie. Probably from ''It looks like he's dangling the puck on a string.''
#:''He dangled around three players and the goalie to score.''
'''to dangle'''  (''transitive'')
#to [[hang]] or [[trail]] something loosely
#:''I like to sit on the edge and '''dangle''' my feet in the water.''

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[roikottaa]], [[riiputtaa]]
*French: [[pendre]], [[pendouiller]]

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
#(intelligence) an agent of one [[intelligence]] [[agency]] or group who pretends to be interested in [[defect]]ing or [[turn]]ing to another intelligence agency or group.
#([[ice hockey]])(slang) the noun used to describe the action of dangling.
#:''That was a sick dangle for a great goal!''

